Maharashtra
Dec 02, 2014
Child Sexual Abuse, Rape
Description:
			In Nalla Sopara locality, a 45-year-old man in Tulinj area was booked for allegedly raping a minor girl on several occasions for the past five months, Nalla Sopara police station API Vitthal Benduta said.

The accused had befriended the victim, who lived in the same locality and helped her by giving money on several occasions. In July this year, he took the victim to his house and spiked her cold drink and raped her, the officer said.

According to the complaint filed by the victim yesterday, the man repeatedly raped her since July. The accused was detained by police yesterday and is being interrogated, but no arrest has been made so far.

A case under IPC sections 376 (rape), 323 (voluntarily causing hurt), 504 (punishment for criminal intimidation), 328 (causing hurt by means of poison, etc) and other relevant sections of POCSO Act in this regard.

